---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Element Snap"
  description="Privacy policy for Element Snap, a Chrome extension for capturing web elements as images."
  canonical="https://lacrima.dev/element-snap/privacy/"
>
  <div class="landing">
    <header class="landing-header">
      <h1>Element Snap</h1>
      <a href="/element-snap" class="landing-back">← Back to Element Snap</a>
    </header>

    <main style="max-width: 680px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 0">
      <h2 style="font-weight: 300; font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem">Privacy Policy</h2>

      <div style="color: #9b9b9f; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.7">
        <p style="margin-bottom: 1rem">
          <strong style="color: #ccc">Last updated:</strong> July 10, 2026.
        </p>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 1rem">
          Element Snap is a Chrome extension that lets you capture visual elements from any
          webpage as high-quality images. This policy describes what data the extension
          accesses, how it is used, and what it does not do.
        </p>

        <h3 style="color: #ccc; font-weight: 400; font-size: 1rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem">Data the extension accesses</h3>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem">
          <strong style="color: #ccc">Active page content.</strong>
          When the user initiates a capture, the extension accesses the DOM of the active tab
          to read computed styles, dimensions, shadows, and render the selected element to an
          image. This access occurs only upon user request and is never transmitted to any server.
        </p>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem">
          <strong style="color: #ccc">User interaction during selection.</strong>
          The extension tracks mouse position and clicks to power the element selector
          (hover-to-preview, click-to-select). This data is processed in real time and is
          never stored or transmitted.
        </p>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 1rem">
          <strong style="color: #ccc">Authentication information.</strong>
          Lifetime license users may sign in with their Google account via Chrome Identity API.
          The extension stores only the authentication token needed to verify license status.
          No Google profile data (name, email, etc.) is accessed or stored.
        </p>

        <h3 style="color: #ccc; font-weight: 400; font-size: 1rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem">Local storage</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 1rem">
          The extension uses <code style="color: #8ab4f8">chrome.storage.local</code> to
          store user preferences (format, scale, background, margins), capture history
          (lifetime license users only), and license status. All data remains exclusively on the user's
          device and can be removed by uninstalling the extension or through Chrome's
          storage settings.
        </p>

        <h3 style="color: #ccc; font-weight: 400; font-size: 1rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem">Third-party services</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem">
          The extension communicates with the following services exclusively for
          authentication and license verification:
        </p>
        <ul style="margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 1.2rem">
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.3rem">
            <strong style="color: #ccc">Supabase</strong> — Google OAuth authentication.
            Only the Chrome Identity token is sent to exchange for a session.
          </li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.3rem">
            <strong style="color: #ccc">Our backend</strong> — License status verification
            and account management. No page content or browsing data is sent.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong style="color: #ccc">Stripe</strong> — Payment processing for the lifetime
            license. Payment occurs on Stripe's secure page. The extension does not access
            credit card data or financial information.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 1rem">
          No analytics services, trackers, advertising SDKs, or user behavior monitoring
          tools are used.
        </p>

        <h3 style="color: #ccc; font-weight: 400; font-size: 1rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem">What Element Snap does not do</h3>
        <ul style="margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 1.2rem">
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.3rem">Does not sell or transfer user data to third parties.</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.3rem">Does not use user data for targeted advertising.</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.3rem">Does not track the user's browsing history.</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.3rem">Does not send captures or page content to external servers.</li>
          <li>Does not use user data for creditworthiness checks or financial activities.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="color: #ccc; font-weight: 400; font-size: 1rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem">Security</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 1rem">
          All image capture and processing occurs locally in the user's browser.
          Communications with the backend and Supabase use encrypted connections (HTTPS).
        </p>

        <h3 style="color: #ccc; font-weight: 400; font-size: 1rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem">Changes to this policy</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 1rem">
          If this policy changes, the "last updated" date will be revised and any
          substantial changes will be announced on the extension's Chrome Web Store page.
        </p>

        <h3 style="color: #ccc; font-weight: 400; font-size: 1rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem">Contact</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 1rem">
          If you have questions about this policy, you can reach us at
          <a href="mailto:lacrimadev@gmail.com" style="color: #8ab4f8">lacrimadev@gmail.com</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </main>

    <footer class="landing-footer">
      <p><a href="mailto:lacrimadev@gmail.com">lacrimadev@gmail.com</a></p>
      <p><a href="/element-snap">← Element Snap</a></p>
    </footer>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
